Object.values()
This method goes into our object, and returns the values of every property as an array.
Here is an example output for using .values():
let footballClubs = {
  chelsea_fc: "England",
  fc_barcelona: "Spain",
  ac_milan: "Italy",
};

console.log(Object.values(footballClubs));
// prints [ 'England', 'Spain', 'Italy' ]

